1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:37,960
=Episode 16=

3
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:40,389
I didn't expect you

4
00:01:40,390 --> 00:01:41,639
to use your flight pass today.

5
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,309
There's only one flight a week.

6
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:45,150
I wanted to see Grandma early.

7
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,790
You're going to investigate
the Xiaosheng case, aren't you?

8
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,229
Don't try to hide it.

9
00:01:53,230 --> 00:01:54,359
When Xiaosheng's

10
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,719
DNA results came out,

11
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,719
it went viral all over the internet.

12
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:58,829
Even my hometown chat groups

13
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:00,550
were buzzing about it.

14
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:03,949
Do you live in Qian Village too?

15
00:02:03,950 --> 00:02:04,439
No.

16
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:06,990
I'm in Outang Village right next to it.
Very close.

17
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,510
Are you going alone?

18
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:11,909
Yes.

19
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:14,200
How about this? I'll be your guide.

20
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,670
I can't just let you
buy me a ticket for nothing.

21
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,399
It's fine.

22
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,029
My local colleagues
will be assisting me.

23
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:20,839
Thanks, though.

24
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:23,439
Can they really know
the area better than I do?

25
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:25,320
I grew up here.

26
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:26,719
I'm still going to pass.

27
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:28,510
We need to keep our distance.

28
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:30,349
Don't be a stranger.

29
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:32,399
Just act like we bumped into each other

30
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,720
while I was visiting home.

31
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:36,159
Besides, helping a judge

32
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:38,390
just shows I'm a good citizen.

33
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,509
Plus,

34
00:02:40,510 --> 00:02:42,320
I'm not representing this case.

35
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,439
I have no skin in the game.

36
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:44,159
Trust me.

37
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:45,789
While you're investigating,

38
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:47,230
I won't say a single word.

39
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:49,880
Excuse me, miss. This is my seat.

40
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:51,719
Oh, please, go ahead. Sorry.

41
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,439
No problem.

42
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:53,880
Let's talk after we land.

43
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:13,029
(Ladies' Room)

44
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:15,200
Where have you been?

45
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,390
You're a few days late.

46
00:03:19,510 --> 00:03:20,880
Thirteen days.

47
00:03:21,350 --> 00:03:23,390
Then you'd better take a test.

48
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,679
I knew that dizzy spell meant something.

49
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:28,070
I told you not to rush into it.

50
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,440
Curse that Xiao Bing.

51
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:35,720
Same world, different dreams, I guess.

52
00:03:36,630 --> 00:03:38,110
What do you mean?

53
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,040
Thinking of a second child?

54
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,189
No way.

55
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:43,230
We're still struggling
with Fei as it is.

56
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:44,880
So,

57
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:48,510
how often do you
and your husband do the deal?

58
00:03:49,790 --> 00:03:51,839
Ever since Fei's accident,

59
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,480
I just haven't been in the mood.

60
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:57,909
That's quite some time.

61
00:03:57,910 --> 00:04:00,230
I've noticed it over the last two years.

62
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,719
The spark in your eyes is gone.

63
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:04,749
Your face has lost its glow.

64
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:05,909
This won't do.

65
00:04:05,910 --> 00:04:08,440
You need to get back
in the game with him.

66
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:13,350
It something you'd fix right away.

67
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,039
Too embarrassed to bring it up?

68
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,390
It's easy.

69
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:19,879
Tell him you want a sibling for Fei.

70
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:20,999
How?

71
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,510
Suggest having a second child.

72
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:23,919
I can't do that.

73
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,439
You don't actually have to do it.

74
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,830
It's just a signal to break the ice.

75
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:34,200
(Ladies' Room)

76
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,560
When will we be there?

77
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,270
Almost there.

78
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:52,509
(Outang Village)

79
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:53,830
Grandma!

80
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:58,039
My Xiang!

81
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:01,390
Xiang, you finally made it!

82
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:06,150
Why do you keep calling me Xiang?

83
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:08,479
Did you forget the sauce jar?

84
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:11,000
It's okay, I had Jiabao bring it.

85
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:13,679
Grandma.

86
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,949
Let me introduce you.

87
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:17,069
This is the judge
from the Qingcheng Court.

88
00:05:17,070 --> 00:05:18,320
His name is Shen.

89
00:05:18,830 --> 00:05:20,149
Hello, Grandma.

90
00:05:20,150 --> 00:05:21,559
I'm Shen Xiezhi.

91
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,709
Good.

92
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:24,030
Good.

93
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:26,829
What a sharp-looking young man.

94
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:28,270
So sharp.

95
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,389
Grandma,

96
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:32,119
I'm going to talk to Auntie Cao

97
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:34,240
about where the judge can stay tonight.

98
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,039
Alright, go ahead.

99
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,470
Keep her company for a bit.

100
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,680
Will do.

101
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:40,590
Have a seat.

102
00:05:41,150 --> 00:05:43,269
Business is booming, Auntie Cao!

103
00:05:43,270 --> 00:05:44,800
Xiang, you're back!

104
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:45,879
Xiang,

105
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:46,679
here.

106
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,509
I've got your fish and tofu.

107
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:50,390
Your grandma ordered them earlier.

108
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,069
Thanks, Auntie Cao.

109
00:05:52,070 --> 00:05:52,709
Auntie Cao,

110
00:05:52,710 --> 00:05:54,509
my friend is here on business.

111
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:56,119
The court booked a hotel for him,

112
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,709
but my phone is dead.

113
00:05:57,710 --> 00:05:59,390
Could you help me contact them?

114
00:05:59,750 --> 00:06:01,270
Sure, I'll give them a call.

115
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,559
Grandma,

116
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,150
how have you been feeling?

117
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,880
Are you doing okay?

118
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,760
She has no father.

119
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:13,440
Her father was a monster.

120
00:06:14,190 --> 00:06:16,240
He was a monster.

121
00:06:22,270 --> 00:06:24,000
Did you have lunch yet?

122
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,269
She has no mother, either.

123
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:27,710
Her mother ran away.

124
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:33,949
Xiang must have
had a hard time growing up.

125
00:06:33,950 --> 00:06:35,710
No, it wasn't hard.

126
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,440
Xiang is good to me.

127
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:41,120
How did you get here?

128
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,920
I flew here.

129
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,149
A plane?

130
00:06:44,150 --> 00:06:45,510
You took a plane?

131
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:47,629
A plane.

132
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:48,509
Yes.

133
00:06:48,510 --> 00:06:49,680
A plane.

134
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:50,509
How fun.

135
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:51,880
Indeed.

136
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,479
What's so fun?

137
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,559
What are you two laughing about?

138
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,510
He said he flew here!

139
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,119
Well, let's go home and cook.

140
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,069
Xiang,

141
00:07:01,070 --> 00:07:03,069
what's your friend's ID number?

142
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:04,439
The hotel needs to confirm the booking.

143
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:06,039
Stay at a hotel?

144
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,149
Don't be so formal!

145
00:07:07,150 --> 00:07:08,709
Come, stay with us.

146
00:07:08,710 --> 00:07:09,920
Wait, Grandma...

147
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:10,879
Come on!

148
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:11,709
I'll cook for you.

149
00:07:11,710 --> 00:07:13,999
Stir-fried dried tofu,
garlic sprouts with smoked pork,

150
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,879
braised fish, and tofu soup.

151
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,360
All the best dishes!

152
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:20,680
Thanks, Auntie Cao.

153
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,630
Thanks, it's fine. I'll carry it myself.

154
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,039
Hurry!

155
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,000
Is the plane fast?

156
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,440
Very fast. I got here in no time.

157
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,479
Tonight,

158
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,590
you'll have to make do
with sleeping here.

159
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,239
It's a bit modest,

160
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:03,000
but this is where I grew up.

161
00:08:03,510 --> 00:08:04,629
It's not modest at all.

162
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:05,509
It's very cozy.

163
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:07,680
It looks very comfortable.
I'll settle in fine.

164
00:08:08,710 --> 00:08:09,389
Okay.

165
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:10,559
Get settled in,

166
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,949
and I'll call you for dinner.

167
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,120
Sounds good.

168
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:28,270
Shen,

169
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:30,920
this is the good stuff. Here,

170
00:08:31,270 --> 00:08:32,149
have a drink.

171
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:34,200
Grandma, I don't drink.

172
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,070
You're leaving?

173
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:37,830
You can't leave yet.

174
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:39,119
Stay the night.

175
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,389
I'm not leaving.

176
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:42,509
Grandma, he didn't say he was leaving.

177
00:08:42,510 --> 00:08:44,470
He said he doesn't drink alcohol.

178
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:46,509
No dogs?

179
00:08:46,510 --> 00:08:49,400
The convenience store
has a dog, but we don't.

180
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:53,160
Grandma.

181
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:54,640
Thank you.

182
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:56,750
Come on.

183
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,520
Bottoms up!

184
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:00,669
Let's...

185
00:09:00,670 --> 00:09:01,319
Alright.

186
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,999
Grandma,
I'll have a quick toast with you.

187
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,269
I still have to work.

188
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:05,440
Okay.

189
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:08,400
Grandma, don't drink too much.

190
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,389
Here, eat.

191
00:09:14,390 --> 00:09:15,680
Thank you, Grandma.

192
00:09:16,630 --> 00:09:17,749
Grandma, here.

193
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:19,070
Have some tofu.

194
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,040
How's my cooking?

195
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:24,629
It's delicious.

196
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:26,509
Delicious, right? Then eat more.

197
00:09:26,510 --> 00:09:27,429
Is it too salty?

198
00:09:27,430 --> 00:09:28,950
If it's good, eat up.

199
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:40,200
Here, drink some water to wash it down.

200
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:43,280
How is my cooking?

201
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:44,959
It's great.

202
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:45,719
Good.

203
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:47,280
If it's good, keep eating.

204
00:09:47,550 --> 00:09:49,470
Don't just eat the dishes,
have more rice.

205
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,199
Here you go.

206
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,879
Grandma, you eat too. Come on.

207
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,200
Of course.

208
00:09:58,150 --> 00:09:59,350
It tastes wonderful.

209
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:01,479
You eat some too.

210
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,680
Alright.

211
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,200
What's wrong, my dear lady?

212
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,640
You're pregnant.

213
00:10:28,150 --> 00:10:29,839
But we clearly used protection.

214
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,710
How did I still end up pregnant?

215
00:10:36,670 --> 00:10:38,280
Did you tamper with something?

216
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,119
My lady,

217
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,920
I wouldn't dare without your okay.

218
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,950
You're the boss of this house.

219
00:10:46,030 --> 00:10:46,999
You call the shots.

220
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,800
I'm crystal clear on that point.

221
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,350
Then, how did this happen?

222
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,590
Move.

223
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:56,590
Well,

224
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,389
protection isn't 100% effective.

225
00:10:58,390 --> 00:11:00,710
There's always
that one lucky survivor, right?

226
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:02,509
Or...

227
00:11:02,510 --> 00:11:05,549
Maybe our genes are just too compatible.

228
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:06,719
Not even a fortress

229
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:09,280
could stop them
from their fortutious meeting.

230
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:13,470
Maybe...

231
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:16,059
Maybe

232
00:11:16,060 --> 00:11:18,400
the baby just couldn't wait to meet us.

233
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,119
Mom.

234
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,400
Right?

235
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:22,909
That's right.

236
00:11:22,910 --> 00:11:24,400
Life is short.

237
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,909
If it's meant to be, it's fate.

238
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:28,669
It just shows how smart this kid is.

239
00:11:28,670 --> 00:11:30,289
It handpicked you two to be the parents.

240
00:11:30,290 --> 00:11:31,520
There's no escaping it now.

241
00:11:33,270 --> 00:11:34,520
Thanks, Mom.

242
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,239
Don't be mad.

243
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,440
Don't touch me.

244
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:42,429
Listen...

245
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:43,680
Don't talk.

246
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:55,269
You're pregnant. Calm down!

247
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:57,149
Stop it. You're pregnant.

248
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:59,590
Be good, okay? You're pregnant now.

249
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:31,720
(Xiang, Daddy, Mommy, Grandma,
Our happy family)

250
00:13:14,670 --> 00:13:16,239
What are you doing
in the middle of the night?

251
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,470
What are you doing?

252
00:13:18,030 --> 00:13:19,029
Why aren't you creeping here

253
00:13:19,030 --> 00:13:20,389
instead of sleeping?

254
00:13:20,390 --> 00:13:21,599
You're banging on it so hard.

255
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,280
How am I supposed to sleep?

256
00:13:23,390 --> 00:13:24,920
Am I being that loud?

257
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:28,839
I wanted to fix it today,
but Grandma wouldn't let me.

258
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,789
Look at this chicken coop.
It's falling apart.

259
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:32,269
She's moving things
in and out every day.

260
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:34,230
What if she throws her back out?

261
00:13:34,430 --> 00:13:36,040
I could only fix it at night.

262
00:13:36,150 --> 00:13:37,800
You should have told me. I'll help.

263
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:44,070
How are you going to help?

264
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:46,920
I drank too much water.

265
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:49,400
I need to use the bathroom.
I'll help when I get back.

266
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:13,149
New pajamas?

267
00:14:13,150 --> 00:14:14,520
They look pretty good.

268
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:16,119
I got them during an online sale.

269
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,520
There's a pair for you and Fei, too.

270
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:23,680
This is too small for Fei.

271
00:14:23,910 --> 00:14:25,110
Look.

272
00:14:25,270 --> 00:14:27,389
It was the last one in stock.

273
00:14:27,390 --> 00:14:29,560
It was basically a giveaway.

274
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:31,239
Even a giveaway should fit.

275
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:33,119
This is for a three or four-year-old.

276
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,239
Fei can't squeeze into this.

277
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,879
Besides, she wouldn't like the color.

278
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:36,669
Tell you what,

279
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:37,359
I'll give it

280
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:39,710
to Old Hu's grandson.

281
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:42,160
No need for that.

282
00:14:42,390 --> 00:14:43,800
Just keep it.

283
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,110
Save it for

284
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:47,470
the second one.

285
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:51,400
Didn't you say

286
00:14:51,510 --> 00:14:54,560
you wanted a son to play soccer with?

287
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:57,470
Lately,

288
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:00,710
I haven't been all that busy.

289
00:15:06,630 --> 00:15:07,920
Uh...

290
00:15:09,390 --> 00:15:11,199
I smell a bit too much like mutton.

291
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,509
Let me go wash up.

292
00:15:12,510 --> 00:15:13,870
I'll be right back.

293
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,520
Yeah.

294
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,870
Just a minute.

295
00:16:15,390 --> 00:16:16,359
Here.

296
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:17,680
Eat up.

297
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:20,320
Go on.

298
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,350
Here.

299
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,920
Good morning, Judge Shen.

300
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:44,470
Morning, Ms. Qin.

301
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,160
This is Qian Village.

302
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:50,839
I'll go ask that gentleman over there.

303
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:51,749
Alright.

304
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:52,990
Sir?

305
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,680
Sorry to bother you,

306
00:16:55,790 --> 00:16:57,999
but could you tell us where
Qian Zhengguo's house is?

307
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:58,749
What?

308
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:01,079
Are you with that woman

309
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,199
from out of town?

310
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,749
A woman from out of town?

311
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:04,319
Yeah.

312
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:06,149
They're over at the ancestral hall,

313
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:07,750
making quite a scene.

314
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:10,079
The people from the court are there.

315
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:11,319
Let's check it out.

316
00:17:11,320 --> 00:17:12,079
Thank you, sir.

317
00:17:12,080 --> 00:17:13,230
Much appreciated.

318
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,279
(Intro to Qian Family Ancestral Hall)

319
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:17,559
Let me say this one more time.

320
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:19,229
You have absolutely no right

321
00:17:19,230 --> 00:17:20,669
to stop me from seeing my brother!

322
00:17:20,670 --> 00:17:23,230
You are breaking the law right now!

323
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,279
You're human traffickers!

324
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:28,030
You're not above the law!

325
00:17:28,230 --> 00:17:30,840
You must be Judge Shen.
I'm court clerk Deng.

326
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:31,599
What's going on?

327
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:32,079
Judge Shen!

328
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:32,709
What happened?

329
00:17:32,710 --> 00:17:33,989
Everyone, quiet down!

330
00:17:33,990 --> 00:17:34,949
Judge Shen,

331
00:17:34,950 --> 00:17:36,949
these human traffickers
are hiding my brother!

332
00:17:36,950 --> 00:17:38,079
We're not human traffickers!

333
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:39,319
Alright, alright.

334
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:41,279
Everyone, settle down. Stop arguing.

335
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:43,310
Where's the village chief?
Get him over here.

336
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:44,640
He's on his way.

337
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:47,600
What is all this commotion?
What are you all doing?

338
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:49,799
Enough! That's enough!

339
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:50,799
Stop fighting, alright?

340
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,230
Enough!

341
00:17:53,670 --> 00:17:55,709
I'm the village chief, Qian Xuedong.

342
00:17:55,710 --> 00:17:57,080
Pardon the mess, Judge.

343
00:17:57,230 --> 00:17:58,119
Hello, sir.

344
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:00,079
I'm Judge Shen Xiezhi from
Qingcheng District

345
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:00,989
People's Court.

346
00:18:00,990 --> 00:18:02,189
Judge Shen, nice to meet you.

347
00:18:02,190 --> 00:18:03,600
Where is Qian Zhengguo's family?

348
00:18:03,990 --> 00:18:05,360
Bring them here.

349
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:06,879
Let's sit down

350
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,079
and

351
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,149
discuss this properly.

352
00:18:09,150 --> 00:18:09,709
Certainly.

353
00:18:09,710 --> 00:18:11,599
Let's head to the ancestral hall.

354
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:12,279
I'll go

355
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:14,080
and fetch the couple shortly.

356
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:15,360
Good.

357
00:18:15,710 --> 00:18:16,879
Alright, alright. Go home.

358
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:17,799
Let's head inside.

359
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:18,989
Let's go.

360
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:20,160
Let's go.

361
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:22,229
Disperse now, disperse!
Stop the shouting.

362
00:18:22,230 --> 00:18:22,989
Deng, take them inside.

363
00:18:22,990 --> 00:18:25,359
Don't you all have work
at home or in the fields?

364
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:26,879
Enough! Dismissed!

365
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,469
Alright, that's enough.
You talk too much.

366
00:18:28,470 --> 00:18:29,389
Move along!

367
00:18:29,390 --> 00:18:30,799
I imagine this is

368
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:32,200
going to take some time.

369
00:18:34,950 --> 00:18:36,550
Head back to your grandma's home.

370
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:38,080
Okay.

371
00:18:38,190 --> 00:18:39,750
We'll have dinner ready for you.

372
00:18:39,990 --> 00:18:41,200
Alright.

373
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:48,519
Here, Judge Shen.

374
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:49,559
Thank you, Chief.

375
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:51,080
You may begin.

376
00:18:53,710 --> 00:18:55,279
I came here

377
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:57,230
just to look into the situation.

378
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:58,599
But since

379
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,759
both parties are present,

380
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:02,030
let's discuss

381
00:19:02,390 --> 00:19:04,790
who Xiaosheng will live with
from here on out.

382
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:05,950
Alright?

383
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,270
Judge,

384
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:10,200
we only came back
for the sake of the child.

385
00:19:10,670 --> 00:19:12,849
Guo was coughing every day in the city.

386
00:19:12,850 --> 00:19:14,599
We did what was best for him.

387
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:16,799
We even gave up
our business in the city.

388
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:17,759
Tell me,

389
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:19,359
how much more could we do?

390
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:20,279
Nie Baomei,

391
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:22,629
stop guilt-tripping my brother, okay?

392
00:19:22,630 --> 00:19:24,189
Your shop was poorly managed.

393
00:19:24,190 --> 00:19:25,759
It was doomed for closure.

394
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:27,599
It's likely that
my brother's health is poor

395
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,759
because of the humidity
in the mountains,

396
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:30,709
You little brat!

397
00:19:30,710 --> 00:19:32,149
How can you say such nasty things?

398
00:19:32,150 --> 00:19:33,559
You called us guilt-tripping?

399
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:34,949
And what's it with the humidity?

400
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:36,229
What are you even talking about?

401
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:37,559
I don't understand a word of this!

402
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:38,319
Alright, alright.

403
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:39,039
Let's not start

404
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:41,039
with such short fuses, okay?

405
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:43,359
We are here with a spirit of negotiation

406
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:44,759
to solve the problem.

407
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,270
Let's all speak calmly.

408
00:19:46,430 --> 00:19:48,200
Judge Shen, look.

409
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:50,030
I don't know about other things,

410
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,510
but when Xiaosheng

411
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:53,519
was entered into the family tree,

412
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:54,469
it was done right here

413
00:19:54,470 --> 00:19:56,030
in this very ancestral hall.

414
00:19:56,630 --> 00:19:58,189
The Village Chief can testify.

415
00:19:58,190 --> 00:19:58,709
That's right.

416
00:19:58,710 --> 00:20:00,389
The child knelt before the whole village

417
00:20:00,390 --> 00:20:02,039
and bowed to the two of us.

418
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:03,839
He said he'd care for us
until our final days.

419
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,880
The boy was absolutely willing.

420
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:08,759
Of course,
it's not like we're just after that.

421
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:10,030
But look at this.

422
00:20:10,150 --> 00:20:12,359
You couldn't even look after
the child yourselves,

423
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,359
yet you blame us who helped him.

424
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:15,429
Where is the justice in that?

425
00:20:15,430 --> 00:20:16,079
Exactly!

426
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:17,640
Who are you to criticize us?

427
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:18,960
You can't have a son yourself,

428
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:20,790
that's your problem.
You should reflect on that!

429
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:22,669
Why you little girl...

430
00:20:22,670 --> 00:20:24,470
How can you be so foul-mouthed?

431
00:20:24,910 --> 00:20:26,149
Watch your tone!

432
00:20:26,150 --> 00:20:28,079
Do you even know any manners?

433
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:29,389
Alright, Mr. Qian.

434
00:20:29,390 --> 00:20:29,759
Sit down.

435
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:31,389
Don't stoop to her level.

436
00:20:31,390 --> 00:20:31,989
She's just a girl.

437
00:20:31,990 --> 00:20:33,079
Yuan Qiaoqiao,

438
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:34,599
no personal attacks.

439
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:35,920
I'll say it one more time.

440
00:20:37,150 --> 00:20:38,440
Judge Shen,

441
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:39,389
we came here today

442
00:20:39,390 --> 00:20:41,359
wanting to solve this problem.

443
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:42,669
Let me propose an idea.

444
00:20:42,670 --> 00:20:44,389
Let's bring the child out

445
00:20:44,390 --> 00:20:46,149
and ask him what he thinks, alright?

446
00:20:46,150 --> 00:20:48,270
It's not like we're stopping him.

447
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,479
The child himself is unwilling, okay?

448
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,359
Qian Zhengguo,

449
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:53,120
can you stop faking it?

450
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,039
Did you hide my brother away?

451
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,200
Why you...

452
00:20:58,320 --> 00:20:59,839
Listen up, Qian Zhengguo,

453
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:01,319
if you had just been polite,

454
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:02,039
our family might've

455
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:03,759
turned a blind eye and let it go.

456
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:05,079
But if you keep being a thug,

457
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:06,479
not only am I taking my brother back,

458
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:07,079
I'll also

459
00:21:07,080 --> 00:21:08,599
hold the entire village responsible!

460
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:09,879
I'll send all of you to prison!

461
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:10,599
You human trafficker!

462
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:11,999
How could you say that?

463
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,719
How can you slander us like that?

464
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:14,959
Who are you calling a trafficker?

465
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:16,959
- Explain yourself!
- Everyone, calm down.

466
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:17,999
Who's a trafficker?

467
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,959
Slander! Who's a trafficker?

468
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:21,559
How did you raise your child?

469
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:22,960
Don't you dare talk about my grandma!

470
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:25,399
Come over here!

471
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,119
Yuan Qiaoqiao!

472
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:27,719
Try saying one more word about her!

473
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,199
Get over here! Come here!

474
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:29,959
Young lady, stop!

475
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:31,039
How can you start hitting people?

476
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:32,320
Speak properly!

477
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:34,480
Stop shouting!

478
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,079
Enough!

479
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:38,400
I won't let you bully my mother!

480
00:21:52,760 --> 00:21:54,079
Judge Shen,

481
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:54,759
do you think

482
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:56,559
he drugged my brother just now?

483
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:59,120
Did you see the way he looked at me?

484
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:03,800
I'm his real family.

485
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:09,920
If I can't get the child back,

486
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:11,959
what's the point of living anymore?

487
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:13,440
Please, don't say that.

488
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:16,920
Let's just calm down for a moment.

489
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:18,480
Let's keep a level head,

490
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,600
and we'll find a way to mediate.

491
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:22,120
Mediate?

492
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:25,240
What is there left to mediate?

493
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:29,959
One of you

494
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:32,360
is Xiaosheng's grandmother,

495
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,760
and the other is his biological sister.

496
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:37,360
These are indisputable facts.

497
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:39,999
Mediation is something we must pursue.

498
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:42,720
But if the process isn't handled well,

499
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,080
given Xiaosheng's young age,

500
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:49,160
it could leave an emotional scar.

501
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,319
Right?

502
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:51,159
So,

503
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,880
let's meet again tomorrow

504
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:55,160
at eight in the morning.

505
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,039
Thank you, Judge Shen.

506
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,360
Thank you.

507
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:04,039
Why didn't you tell me

508
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:06,120
about Ge's condition sooner?

509
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,879
I would have assigned you fewer cases,

510
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:09,640
so you'd have less overtime work.

511
00:23:10,560 --> 00:23:11,799
In our court,

512
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:13,599
every judge handles
so many cases a year.

513
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,879
If you assigned me fewer,

514
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,879
the others would be swamped.

515
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:19,320
Special circumstances
require special treatment.

516
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,279
What's so special?

517
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:22,359
Everyone has their own difficulties.

518
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:24,039
It's okay, I can manage.

519
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:24,799
And

520
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,959
I'll ask for leave if I need to.

521
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:28,679
Just use your own judgment.

522
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,599
Don't push yourself.

523
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,159
Don't burn yourself out.

524
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,359
Don't worry, I know my limits.

525
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:34,880
When is the surgery scheduled?

526
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:38,959
I almost forgot why I came today.

527
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,759
It's quite a coincidence.

528
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:41,319
What is?

529
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,399
The plaintiff in this case

530
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:45,440
is Ge Ying's attending physician.

531
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:46,439
Really?

532
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:47,359
What a coincidence.

533
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:49,039
The case is in the Mediation Room now.

534
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:50,879
My point is, could it be

535
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:52,800
reassigned to someone else?

536
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:54,519
I need to recuse myself.

537
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:55,399
Alright.

538
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,919
We'll just follow the standard

539
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:58,119
recusal procedure.

540
00:23:58,120 --> 00:23:58,719
Yes.

541
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:01,080
But the surgery still needs to be done.

542
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:02,600
It's not that urgent.

543
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:05,599
No, it's actually quite urgent.

544
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:06,879
It's okay, Tianhai is big.

545
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,439
I'll find another hospital.

546
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:10,440
There are plenty of experts out there.

547
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:13,599
By the way,

548
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:15,399
I remember Shen Xiezhi's mother

549
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,920
is in the breast department.

550
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:17,959
At the People's Hospital.

551
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,800
I think she's even the department head.

552
00:24:20,320 --> 00:24:22,279
Judge Shen's mother is a doctor?

553
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:22,999
That's right.

554
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:25,680
She was invited for
that breast health lecture last time?

555
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:30,439
Talk about searching
far and wide for someone.

556
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:32,040
Wow.

557
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,199
You're back.

558
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:36,680
How did the mediation go?

559
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:38,999
Not only did they not settle,

560
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:41,160
they almost started fighting.

561
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,040
Where's your grandma?

562
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:45,160
She's resting inside.

563
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:46,759
I'll get you a glass of water.

564
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:47,839
No need, it's fine.

565
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:49,400
I'm not thirsty. Sit, please.

566
00:24:55,680 --> 00:24:57,439
I'm quite troubled right now.

567
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:58,679
I just want to rest for a bit.

568
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,760
What's the matter? Is it that serious?

569
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:03,840
Hypothetically,

570
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:06,759
suppose there's a situation like this.

571
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:08,559
A young child was forced to leave

572
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:09,479
his biological parents

573
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:10,879
for some reasons

574
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:11,959
and grew up in another family.

575
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:13,519
Now his biological family has found him

576
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:15,920
and wants to take him back
no matter what.

577
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:17,079
On the other hand,

578
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,639
it's the familiar environment

579
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:19,919
he's lived in for years.

580
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:22,559
His foster parents are also good to him.

581
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:23,199
How do you think

582
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,359
this child would choose?

583
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:25,920
Which side should he stay with?

584
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:27,960
How old is the child?

585
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:30,199
Which side share a deeper bond with him?

586
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:32,040
After all, blood is thicker than water.

587
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,319
True.

588
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:36,039
Biological ties can't be severed.

589
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:37,239
But from another perspective,

590
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,559
one side is

591
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:41,199
a sudden change
to a strange environment,

592
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,599
while the other is a familiar,

593
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:44,039
loving environment.

594
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:46,720
It's only natural for him to choose

595
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,040
to stay where he feels safe.

596
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:51,639
An unfamiliar place
can become familiar over time.

597
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:52,119
Right.

598
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:54,200
He can slowly get used to it.

599
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:59,680
You're not wrong about that.

600
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:02,080
It's also an opportunity for both sides.

601
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:11,720
Before we begin today,

602
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:14,040
I'd like to show you all a video.

603
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:45,400
Judge Shen,

604
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:47,280
what is the meaning of this?

605
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:50,239
The little yellow duck in this video

606
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:51,359
saw this golden retriever

607
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:53,720
the very moment it was born.

608
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:54,959
It looks at the dog

609
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,559
as its own mother,

610
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,160
following it wherever it goes.

611
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:01,920
And what are you trying to say?

612
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:04,680
Please, let the judge finish speaking.

613
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:06,479
The Qian family claims

614
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:08,039
a nurturing bond

615
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:09,440
with Xiaosheng,

616
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,559
one that he is accustomed to.

617
00:27:11,560 --> 00:27:13,440
and deeply attached to.

618
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:15,159
Yet, the Yuans' biological ties

619
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:16,399
to Guo

620
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:18,200
cannot be erased.

621
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:19,199
I know that

622
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:20,719
both sides only want

623
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:23,119
the boy to grow up healthy and happy.

624
00:27:23,120 --> 00:27:24,959
This lawsuit is about ensuring he gets

625
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:26,759
the best possible arrangement.

626
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:28,639
Xiaosheng has always been

627
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:30,640
perfectly fine living with us.

628
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:32,359
Therefore, I am proposing that

629
00:27:32,360 --> 00:27:33,519
for this summer break,

630
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:36,279
Xiaosheng lives with Ms. Liu's family

631
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:37,840
for a period of time.

632
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:39,799
Then we can see
how to proceed from there.

633
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:41,119
Unacceptable!

634
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:42,480
I don't agree.

635
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:44,200
Out of the question!

636
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:46,680
I agree.

637
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:50,360
Grandma, what are you saying?

638
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:51,679
Judge Shen,

639
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:52,639
we are very grateful

640
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:54,759
for the help you've given our family.

641
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:55,640
But

642
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:56,999
you have no idea how our family

643
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:59,160
has suffered all these years.

644
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,959
If I hadn't found my brother,
that would be one thing.

645
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:03,279
But now that I've finally found him,

646
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:05,720
I refuse to risk losing him again.

647
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,919
What can a single summer achieve?

648
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:08,719
Once it's over,

649
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:10,599
he just goes back to their house?

650
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:11,799
I won't allow it.

651
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:14,119
As if I'd allow that!

652
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:15,839
Why should we share the child

653
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:17,960
we raised ourselves?

654
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:19,679
Besides,

655
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:20,919
once the summer is over,

656
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:23,359
whether you'll return the child

657
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:25,080
is another matter entirely.

658
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:26,919
If Xiaosheng disowns us,

659
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:30,800
what will we do?

660
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:32,479
Does your family have no shame?

661
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:34,199
How can you speak like that, young lady?

662
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:34,999
Alright, alright.

663
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:37,160
Both sides, please calm down, okay?

664
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:40,599
No! I absolutely disagree!

665
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:42,000
Qiaoqiao.

666
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:46,239
If you both

667
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:48,400
continue to argue like this

668
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:50,199
and cause such a scene,

669
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,280
the only one who gets hurt is Xiaosheng.

670
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,439
Furthermore, we are here today

671
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:56,720
with the intention
of solving the problem.

672
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,679
Please, both of you consider

673
00:28:58,680 --> 00:29:00,479
each other's current situation.

674
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:02,439
I believe this arrangement

675
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,959
for Xiaosheng

676
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:05,719
is a sound and doable one.

677
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:08,080
It is also an opportunity

678
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:09,680
for both sides.

679
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,120
Mom.

680
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:18,399
Guo!

681
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:20,120
Why are you here?

682
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:22,760
Mom, I heard everything just now.

683
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:25,360
I will never disown you.

684
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:27,479
You raised me.

685
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:29,880
I know and appreciate everything
you've done for me.

686
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:35,360
For this summer break,

687
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:37,959
I want to go with them.

688
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:38,959
You can't go!

689
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:41,679
What do you know? You can't go!

690
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:42,519
Mom.

691
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:44,439
I am grateful that you raised me.

692
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:45,879
But they are my own flesh and blood.

693
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,199
You are all my family.

694
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,680
I don't want you to be enemies.

695
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:50,840
Mom.

696
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:52,920
Please, just let me go.

697
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:58,640
What should we do?

698
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:02,200
Guo.

699
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:05,560
Grandma will personally
come to pick you up,

700
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:08,240
and then I will bring you back.

701
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:27,080
Ms. Nie,

702
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,480
do you agree?

703
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:48,240
What about Mr. Qian?

704
00:30:49,360 --> 00:30:53,000
I'll go talk to him.

705
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,400
I'll talk to him.

706
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:57,959
Son,

707
00:30:57,960 --> 00:31:00,400
I'd hate to see you go.

708
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:16,800
(Outpatient Clinic, People's Hospital)

709
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:34,839
Surgery is an option.

710
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:36,200
Prepare for admission.

711
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:41,760
That's wonderful!

712
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:43,719
Today is my grandma's birthday.

713
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:45,479
I'm cooking the dishes she likes

714
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:47,640
to give her a happy birthday.

715
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:49,200
The tofu is cut.

716
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:50,800
Does it smell good?

717
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,800
It looks delicious already.

718
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:58,080
This time, I really have to thank you.

719
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:00,519
How are you going to thank me?

720
00:32:00,520 --> 00:32:01,719
Have some more soup.

721
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:02,679
And use less salt.

722
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:04,400
How's it coming along?

723
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,880
- Almost ready, Grandma.
- Let me see.

724
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:07,160
Let me have a look.

725
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:10,359
Taste it.

726
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:11,840
Don't burn yourself.

727
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:15,800
There's no flavor at all.

728
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:18,320
Without salt, you'll have no strength.

729
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:20,799
Grandma, don't add any more, stop!

730
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:22,040
I'll add it.

731
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:23,199
Grandma,

732
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:25,479
go to the door
and peel the garlic, okay?

733
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:26,839
- Garlic? You need garlic?
- Yes.

734
00:32:26,840 --> 00:32:27,559
We need garlic.

735
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:28,760
Okay.

736
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:30,359
And the green beans too.

737
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:31,399
Stir-fry them.

738
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:32,640
Okay.

739
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:34,999
Dinner will be on the table in a moment.

740
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,160
Got it.

741
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:39,160
That was a close call.

742
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:42,440
Adding the tofu now.

743
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:49,360
Not bad, right?

744
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:56,839
Fine wine for honored guests,

745
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:58,920
and may life get better with every bite.

746
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:00,359
Be patient, Grandma.

747
00:33:00,360 --> 00:33:01,759
The guest isn't at the table yet.

748
00:33:01,760 --> 00:33:04,400
Hurry.

749
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:07,920
Grandma.

750
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:09,319
It's the weekend,

751
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:11,879
and my work here is finally finished.

752
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:14,120
Let me have
a proper drink with you tonight.

753
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:14,719
Alright.

754
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:16,120
To your health.

755
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:18,760
As if you can handle your liquor.

756
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:21,039
Take it easy.

757
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:22,680
You too, Grandma.

758
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:25,000
This wine smells wonderful.

759
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:25,599
Right?

760
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:26,279
Yes.

761
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,600
Grandma has kept this wine
for ten years.

762
00:33:29,840 --> 00:33:31,240
Thirty years?

763
00:33:31,560 --> 00:33:34,240
Thirty years!

764
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,760
You should have said so earlier!

765
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:39,760
It would be worth a fortune
if you'd saved it to sell.

766
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:42,399
Grandma,

767
00:33:42,400 --> 00:33:43,719
today is your birthday.

768
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:45,279
Let's drink

769
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:46,119
to your health.

770
00:33:46,120 --> 00:33:48,119
I wish you a very happy birthday.

771
00:33:48,120 --> 00:33:50,840
May your live long and prosper.

772
00:33:51,080 --> 00:33:52,160
Bottoms up!

773
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:53,439
I'll finish mine too.

774
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:54,039
I'm done.

775
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:55,600
I'll join you.

776
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:56,039
Cheers!

777
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:58,560
Stop drinking. Don't drink too much.

778
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:04,279
Grandma,

779
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:06,080
I wish you a happy birthday.

780
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:08,039
I am happy!

781
00:34:08,040 --> 00:34:08,919
Okay, eat up.

782
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,199
Let's dig in.

783
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:12,200
Eat up, everyone.

784
00:34:12,240 --> 00:34:13,399
Come, let's eat.

785
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:14,480
Okay.

786
00:34:15,160 --> 00:34:17,160
Grandma, we'll have cake later.

787
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:19,760
(May wealth flow in)
Here, Grandma.

788
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:21,840
Don't drink that much.

789
00:34:23,280 --> 00:34:24,559
Grandma, wait for me here a moment.

790
00:34:24,560 --> 00:34:26,200
I'm going to get something for you.

791
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:30,480
What is she saying?

792
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:33,600
She's going to get you something.

793
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:37,680
Look.

794
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:41,280
This is the birthday gift I got for you.

795
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:42,720
Do you like it?

796
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:48,840
Having the honor

797
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:51,680
to wear this once in my lifetime

798
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:55,680
means I can
leave this world behind with pride.

799
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:58,000
Stop! Don't be silly.

800
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,839
Try it on and see if it fits.

801
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:01,280
Go on, put it on.

802
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:06,880
Xiang,

803
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:08,560
my dear Xiang,

804
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:10,280
you've really

805
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:12,880
given me a proud moment today.

806
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:18,039
I feel so honored.

807
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:19,679
Thank you, Xiang.

808
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:21,159
This is a happy occasion.

809
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:23,279
Let's have no more talk of bad luck.

810
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,320
Do you hear me? Don't forget.

811
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:26,880
Come now, sit down.

812
00:35:27,240 --> 00:35:29,640
You shouldn't say things like that
on your birthday.

813
00:35:30,600 --> 00:35:31,800
You look lovely.

814
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:35,479
Let's have some cake.

815
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:36,319
Grandma.

816
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,959
I'll light the candles for you.

817
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:39,360
Make a wish.

818
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:51,359
♪Happy birthday to you♪

819
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:54,920
♪Happy birthday to you♪

820
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:59,320
♪Happy birthday to you♪

821
00:35:59,680 --> 00:36:04,000
♪Happy birthday to you♪

822
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:13,639
To a long and healthy life!

823
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:14,679
A long and healthy life!

824
00:36:14,680 --> 00:36:15,439
Happy birthday!

825
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:17,000
I'm so happy.

826
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:22,880
Grandma, slow down!

827
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:26,319
Don't drink like that again, okay?

828
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:27,279
You're really scaring me.

829
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,840
You can't just down it all at once.

830
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:30,919
Were you

831
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,720
sneaking drinks when I wasn't home?

832
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:36,440
No.

833
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:37,279
Easy now.

834
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:38,359
Take it easy, Grandma.

835
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:40,239
Come on, Grandma.

836
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:41,800
Sit back a bit more.

837
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,280
Lean on the pillow.

838
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:46,000
Just lean back, Grandma.

839
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:54,840
Sit down, dear.

840
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:57,640
Promise me
you won't drink like that again.

841
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:01,040
I was just so happy today.

842
00:37:02,080 --> 00:37:04,160
But you shouldn't overdo it.

843
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:07,680
My dear,

844
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:09,840
allow me to speak

845
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:12,200
from the bottom of my heart.

846
00:37:14,520 --> 00:37:16,160
Go ahead, I'm listening.

847
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:20,520
My Xiang...

848
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:26,240
She has had such a hard life.

849
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:29,440
She has suffered so much

850
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:32,160
since she was a little girl.

851
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:35,360
Grandma, why are you bringing
this up again?

852
00:37:37,160 --> 00:37:39,279
The one I worry about most

853
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,360
is my Xiang.

854
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:44,280
I just want her

855
00:37:45,080 --> 00:37:46,800
to find someone

856
00:37:47,560 --> 00:37:49,200
who will truly love her

857
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,800
and take the best care of her.

858
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:53,600
Grandma.

859
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:54,919
Grandma!

860
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:57,320
Please don't say things like that
to Judge Shen.

861
00:38:30,240 --> 00:38:32,360
Hi, Judge Shen.

862
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:35,519
Trust me, Judge Shen.

863
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:36,559
With my intelligence,

864
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:38,920
I can definitely be an asset to you.

865
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:41,559
Regardless,

866
00:38:41,560 --> 00:38:43,599
I know you aren't that kind of person.

867
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:44,479
Please, I'm begging you.

868
00:38:44,480 --> 00:38:45,600
Just work with me.

869
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:48,320
Report this to the police.
We have to call the police...

870
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:52,200
You and Ms. Qin really
do coordinate flawlessly.

871
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:07,280
Why are you sitting on the floor?

872
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:12,600
I'll join you for a bit.

873
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,440
What is it?

874
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:34,320
Qin Rui...

875
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:38,800
There are things

876
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:42,000
I've been keeping to myself.

877
00:39:45,260 --> 00:39:51,020
♪When a leaf can't find a place to fall♪

878
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:55,640
I want to be the one
who looks after you.

879
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,680
But I'm conflicted.

880
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:05,960
I don't want us to repeat the mistakes

881
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:08,040
of Jiang Feng and Lou Yue.

882
00:40:09,640 --> 00:40:10,879
(Judge Jiang,)

883
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:12,559
(is this the first time you've heard)

884
00:40:12,560 --> 00:40:14,839
(of the recusal rules
for judges and lawyers?)

885
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:17,319
If either of us makes a sacrifice today,

886
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:18,319
won't that become

887
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:20,399
grounds for emotional blackmail later?

888
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:21,919
I would never blackmail you.

889
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,440
I'm not resigning.

890
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:30,799
♪I want to be in your world♪

891
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:34,690
♪And cast away my disguise♪

892
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:37,680
It's okay.

893
00:40:41,900 --> 00:40:43,760
You don't know me.

894
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:45,720
Ever since I was a child,

895
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:48,840
I've wanted to be a lawyer
at a top-tier law firm.

896
00:40:49,200 --> 00:40:50,680
My biggest dream

897
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:53,120
was to make a fortune,
become successful,

898
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:55,760
and give Grandma a good life

899
00:40:55,800 --> 00:40:58,760
as soon as possible.

900
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:06,920
And I also know that

901
00:41:07,520 --> 00:41:08,839
you have always

902
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:10,680
wanted to be an exceptional judge.

903
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:14,600
You won't stay
at Qingcheng Court forever, either.

904
00:41:15,520 --> 00:41:16,440
Right?

905
00:41:16,900 --> 00:41:18,810
♪I've decided♪

906
00:41:19,870 --> 00:41:22,510
Do you think turning down a promotion
is a sacrifice?

907
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:27,919
I won't accept your sacrifice.

908
00:41:27,920 --> 00:41:29,079
Face yourself

909
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:30,359
and face reality.

910
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:31,860
It's better to end it now.

911
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:37,480
♪Let me be your safe haven♪

912
00:41:37,730 --> 00:41:40,439
♪I want to be in your world♪

913
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:41,389
Thank you

914
00:41:41,390 --> 00:41:44,689
♪And cast away my disguise♪

915
00:41:44,690 --> 00:41:47,240
for giving me such a wonderful night.

916
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:55,499
♪I want to be in your world♪

917
00:41:55,500 --> 00:41:59,109
♪I'll be your shelter♪

918
00:41:59,110 --> 00:42:05,970
♪I'll be there for you
until the very end♪

919
00:42:06,100 --> 00:42:09,669
♪I want to be in your world♪

920
00:42:09,670 --> 00:42:13,269
♪And forget the passage of time♪

921
00:42:13,270 --> 00:42:20,140
♪You are the only one that I see♪

922
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:23,839
♪I want to be in your world♪

923
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:27,590
♪Everything is no longer faraway♪

924
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:29,639
Those two are clearly
in love with each other.

925
00:42:29,640 --> 00:42:31,559
Aren't they your friends too?

926
00:42:31,560 --> 00:42:33,079
How can you break them up?

927
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:33,999
Do you know what it means

928
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:35,999
to make a clean break
and cut your losses?

929
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:36,879
A great judge

930
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,239
being with a great lawyer

931
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:39,799
can only end in tragedy.

932
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:40,639
Are we supposed to wait

933
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:42,960
until they have a child
to talk about breaking up?

934
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

935
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

936
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

937
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

938
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

939
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

940
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

941
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

942
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

943
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

944
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

945
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

946
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

947
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

948
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

949
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

950
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

951
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

952
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

953
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

954
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

955
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

956
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

957
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

958
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

959
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

960
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

961
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

962
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

963
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

964
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

965
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

966
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

967
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

968
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

969
